http://www.cs.cmu.edu/People/roc/Lackwit.html
[New version as of June 4, 1999: ftp://majesty.fac.cs.cmu.edu/lackwit-dist/sun4_55.tar.gz]

The Lackwit tar file extracts into the current directory.

When running the demo:
Change Makefile:
  -include Makefile.@sys
  +include Makefile.solaris
Create Makefile.solaris:
  cp -p Makefile.sun4_413 Makefile.solaris
Edit Makefile.solaris:
  -KRBINCDIR=/usr/local/include
  -KRBLIBDIR=/usr/local/lib
  +KRBINCDIR=/usr/include/kerberos
  +KRBLIBDIR=/usr/lib
  -DESINCDIR=/usr/local/include
  +DESINCDIR=/usr/include/des/
I couldn't find libdes* in /uns/lib/, /usr/lib/, or /usr/local/lib/.  Where
is it?

Each time before I run Lackwit, do (in a separate shell, so I don't
contaminate my other work):
  setenv PATH $LACKWIT_HOME/bin:$PATH
Then do:
  EmitHeaders $LACKWIT_HOME/lib/Default.sigs 
  gcc -c $LACKWIT_HOME/lib/libc.c -o /dev/null
One of these:
  make
  Lackwit foo2.c
Then, to query:
  BackEnd

Even after all that, I got lots of errors, and the -ldes link step
(obviously) failed; but the database did get fully built and seems to work.
I should perhaps try to run Lackwit on a (much) simpler example.

To find the variables that share types with a given variable, do
"searchlocal procname:varname", eg "searchlocal real_count:start".

